 timely book will appeal to all interested in world cinemas, in North African and Islamic cultures, and in the role of cinema as a vehicle for the expression of contested identities. By the author of the critically-acclaimed Contemporary French Cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion pictureszAlgeriaxHistory. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAlgerian national cinema.  aBlack October.  aBoumediene era.  aIslamic states.  aLa Citadelle.  aLettre à ma soeur.  aTahia ya didou.  aclash of civilisations.  anationalist ideology.  apostcolonial state.  aself-imposed incarceration.1 aAustin, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614117040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141170423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141170/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles